						               													<description>Thrive is an educational board game about health. The aim of the game is to reach your own goals by good choices. The winner is the first person to have sufficient cash to pay for their fourth goal. Each player takes a goal pad and writes four goals, ranging from short to long term, in the spaces. Short term goals are worth $50,000 long term goals are worth $1,000,000. The first player to $1,000,000 wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game board resembles a square monopoly-style board with players moving their tokens on the outer track. A player is chosen as the banker for issuing starting money, collecting fines, etc. Players keep track of their points and earns money as they go around the track. Whenever a goal is paid in full, the score peg returns to zero and the player works towards another goal.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
